@startuml
!include ../includes/appsec-style.puml
title AppSec Process 03: Static Analysis (GHAS + Coverity + SonarQube) — Analysis & Triage

' Purpose: Produce actionable static-analysis findings and route them using AppCode-based ownership.

start

partition "Run Scans" {
  :SonarQube analysis (quality + security rules);
  :GHAS CodeQL analysis;
  :Coverity scan (gap languages / deep analysis);
}

partition "Normalize" {
  :Map finding -> CWE / category;
  :Enrich with repo + branch + commit;
  :Correlate to AppCode;
  :Dedupe across tools;
}

partition "Prioritize" {
  if (Exploitability + impact high?) then (Yes)
    :Mark critical/high;
  else (No)
    :Mark medium/low;
  endif
}

partition "Assign & Track" {
  :Create/Update ticket (AppCode + owning team);
  :Set SLA by severity;
  if (Needs exception?) then (Yes)
    :Time-boxed waiver + compensating control;
  else (No)
    :Remediation plan;
  endif
}

partition "Close" {
  :Verify fix via re-scan;
  :Update metrics (MTTR, reopen rate);
}

note right
Key message: **One triage path** for multiple static tools.
AppCode prevents orphaned findings.
end note

stop
@enduml
